result.execSummary:
The defendant Cynthia L Nelson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:46 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Joey Roeth.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 in 2016CF49 and count 2 in 2016CF55.  State concurs.  Atty Roeth concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 as charged on 2016CF49 and orders counts 2 & 3 be dismissed and read-in.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 2 on 2016CF55, striking the repeater and orders counts 1 & 3 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.  

State moves to dismiss the speeding citation.  Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to 2016TR589.  Court finds the defendant guilty and sentences the defendant to:  the forfeiture and costs on the citation.  60 days to pay or payment plan.  AODA.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2016CF49

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.

-Court costs.
-AODA and any follow-up.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
